n4538\t- **Files added** (1):\n4539\t  - `peek/src/server/mutations/__tests__/reward-config.test.ts` — 32\n4540\t    unit tests across allowlist derivation, value validator, schema,\n4541\t    definition wiring, and full runner-orchestrated FR-14 path for\n4542\t    `reward_config.update`.\n4543\t\n4544\t- **Test groups**:\n4545\t  - `PEEK_REWARD_CONFIG_EDITABLE_KEYS` (2 tests): every editable key\n4546\t    is registered with a non-`unknown` expected type; the seed list\n4547\t    includes `points_per_dollar`, `reward_pool_fee_share`, and\n4548\t    `sol_crate_min_value`.\n4549\t  - `validateRewardConfigValueForKey` (9 tests): integer happy/sad,\n4550\t    lamports happy / negative / non-numeric, float (decimal accepted,\n4551\t    pure-integer rejected as `expected_float_with_decimal`,\n4552\t    non-finite rejected), ratio in-range / out-of-range, unknown key\n4553\t    short-circuits.\n4554\t  - `rewardConfigUpdateInputSchema` (8 tests): valid shape, trim,\n4555\t    disallowed key reject, malformed value reject (with field error\n4556\t    on `value`), missing `confirm` reject, `confirm: false` reject,\n4557\t    empty value after trim reject, strict extra-fields reject.\n4558\t  - `rewardConfigUpdateMutation definition` (1 test): pins\n4559\t    `actionId=\"reward_config.update\"` and\n4560\t    `resourceType=\"reward_config\"` so audit-row contract regressions\n4561\t    fail a test rather than ship silently.\n4562\t  - `reward_config.update via runPeekMutation` (12 tests):\n4563\t    - **Allowed integer key success** — emits\n4564\t      `peek.change.applied` with `[{ field: \"value\", before: \"100\",\n4565\t      after: \"200\" }]`, transaction begins exactly once, never rolls\n4566\t      back, SELECT precedes UPDATE, UPDATE binds\n4567\t      `[\"200\", \"points_per_dollar\"]` and includes\n4568\t      `update reward_config` + `updated_at = now()` in the SQL,\n4569\t      audit's `requestId` + `actorEmail` + `route` round-trip, and\n4570\t      audit is written on the in-tx Sql so the change + audit row are\n4571\t      atomic.\n4572\t    - **Allowed ratio key success** — applied audit emitted with the\n4573\t      0.1 → 0.25 diff for `reward_pool_fee_share`.\n4574\t    - **Disallowed key** — schema-layer reject;\n4575\t      `peek.change.rejected` with `rejectionReason: \"invalid_input\"`,\n4576\t      `fieldErrors.key` populated, transaction never opened.\n4577\t    - **Malformed integer value (1.5)** — schema-layer reject;\n4578\t      `fieldErrors.value` populated, transaction never opened.\n4579\t    - **Out-of-range ratio (1.5)** — schema-layer reject via\n4580\t      `superRefine`; `fieldErrors.value` populated, transaction\n4581\t      never opened.\n4582\t    - **Missing confirm** — schema-layer reject;\n4583\t      `fieldErrors.confirm` populated, transaction never opened.\n4584\t    - **Confirm: false** — schema-layer reject; transaction never\n4585\t      opened.\n4586\t    - **No-op (value unchanged)** — `execution_failed: noop_value`;\n4587\t      transaction begins once + rolls back, SELECT runs, UPDATE\n4588\t      never runs, `payload.changes === null`.\n4589\t    - **Allowlisted key missing in DB** —\n4590\t      `execution_failed: unknown_key: points_per_dollar`; transaction\n4591\t      begins + rolls back, SELECT runs, UPDATE never runs.\n4592\t    - **Non-admin (business) actor** — runner short-circuits before\n4593\t      `sql.begin`; `peek.change.rejected` with `rejectionReason:\n4594\t      \"unauthorized\"` and zero SQL calls.\n4595\t    - **Null actor role** — same denial path; `rejectionReason:\n4596\t      \"unauthorized\"`.\n4597\t\n4598\t- **Test scaffolding parity with `kol-rate.test.ts` /\n4599\t  `fraud-flag.test.ts` / `dogpile.test.ts`**:\n4600\t  - `createAuditWriter()` records `eventType` + `payload` + which\n4601\t    `Sql` was used.\n4602\t  - `createSqlMock()` emulates `sql.begin` and the tagged-template\n4603\t    invocation pattern, returning the `existingRow` for SELECTs\n4604\t    (shaped as `{key, value}` to match\n4605\t    `reward-config.ts:fetchExistingRow`) and optionally rejecting\n4606\t    UPDATEs via `failOnUpdate`.\n4607\t  - `REGISTRY` is a frozen single-entry registry holding only\n4608\t    `rewardConfigUpdateMutation` so the runner test path doesn't pull\n4609\t    in unrelated production mutations.\n4610\t\n4611\t- **Targeted checks** (CLAUDE.md TS rule):\n4612\t  - `cd peek && pnpm lint` ✅\n4613\t  - `cd peek && pnpm typecheck` ✅\n4614\t  - `cd peek && pnpm test --run` ✅ (83 files, 968/968 — +32 new\n4615\t    tests, no regressions; full suite green).\n4616\t\n4617\t- **Next**: `[frontend] Wire mutation UIs (KOL rate, fraud flag\n4618\t  status, Dogpile cancel, reward config edit) with old/new\n4619\t  confirmation, role-aware visibility, and rejection messaging.`\n4620\t## Iteration 151 — 2026-04-26T19:24:46Z — OK\n4621\t- **Log**: iteration-151.log\n4622\t\n4623\t\n4624\t\n4625\t## Iteration 152 — 2026-04-26 — Mutation UI wiring\n4626\t\n4627\t- **Item**: `[frontend] Wire mutation UIs (KOL rate, fraud flag\n4628\t  status, Dogpile cancel, reward config edit) with old/new\n4629\t  confirmation, role-aware visibility, and rejection messaging.`\n4630\t\n4631\t- **Files added** (5):\n4632\t  - `peek/src/server/actions/peek-mutations.ts` — four\n4633\t    `\"use server\"` Next.js Server Actions\n4634\t    (`kolRateUpdateAction`, `fraudFlagStatusUpdateAction`,\n4635\t    `dogpileCancelAction`, `rewardConfigUpdateAction`) and the\n4636\t    shared `PeekMutationActionState` shape consumed by\n4637\t    `useActionState`. Each action resolves the verified actor\n4638\t    via `getPeekActorContext()`, reads the `x-request-id`\n4639\t    header, dispatches through `runPeekMutation` (so the\n4640\t    FR-2 role check + FR-14 audit pipeline runs identically\n4641\t    to a direct invocation), and `revalidatePath`s the source\n4642\t    admin route on success. Errors round-trip with their\n4643\t    runner reason (`unauthorized` / `invalid_input` /\n4644\t    `execution_failed` / ...) plus zod `fieldErrors`.\n4645\t  - `peek/src/components/mutations/mutation-feedback.tsx` —\n4646\t    pure presenter that maps `PeekMutationActionState` to\n4647\t    operator-friendly status / alert lines with reason-specific\n4648\t    copy and per-field error bullets.\n4649\t  - `peek/src/components/mutations/kol-rate-mutation-form.tsx` —\n4650\t    inline form with editable `wallet` + `rateBps` inputs,\n4651\t    `old: …` adjacent to each input for visual diff, and\n4652\t    submit button. Wires `useActionState(kolRateUpdateAction)`.\n4653\t  - `peek/src/components/mutations/fraud-flag-mutation-form.tsx`\n4654\t    — inline form whose `nextStatus` `<select>` exposes only\n4655\t    matrix-allowed transitions for the row's current status\n4656\t    (mirrors `FRAUD_FLAG_ALLOWED_TRANSITIONS`); renders\n4657\t    nothing when no transitions are admissible.\n4658\t  - `peek/src/components/mutations/dogpile-cancel-mutation-form.tsx`\n4659\t    — single-button form rendered only for rows whose status\n4660\t    is exactly `scheduled`; shows the implicit\n4661\t    `scheduled → cancelled` diff inline.\n4662\t  - `peek/src/components/mutations/reward-config-mutation-form.tsx`\n4663\t    — inline value editor with explicit confirmation checkbox\n4664\t    (FR-14: `confirm: literal(true)`); the submit button stays\n4665\t    disabled until the operator types a value that differs\n4666\t    from the current row and checks the confirmation box, so\n4667\t    the UI mirrors the engine's no-op rejection rule.\n4668\t\n4669\t- **Files modified** (7):\n4670\t  - `peek/src/components/growth-kol-table.tsx` — accepts\n4671\t    `canMutateKolRate` (default false). When true, appends an\n4672\t    \"Edit rate\" column rendering `KolRateMutationForm` per row.\n4673\t  - `peek/src/components/dogpile-events-table.tsx` — accepts\n4674\t    `canCancelDogpile` (default false). When true, appends a\n4675\t    \"Cancel\" column; non-`scheduled` rows render an empty cell.\n4676\t  - `peek/src/components/fraud-flags-table.tsx` — accepts\n4677\t    `canTransitionFraudFlag` (default false). When true,\n4678\t    appends a \"Transition\" column.\n4679\t  - `peek/src/components/reward-config-table.tsx` — accepts\n4680\t    `canEditRewardConfig` (default false) and `editableKeys`\n4681\t    (default `[]`). When admin and key is in the allowlist\n4682\t    (and `expectedType \\!== \"unknown\"`), renders the edit form;\n4683\t    otherwise the cell is empty so an operator cannot submit\n4684\t    a request the engine would reject.\n4685\t  - `peek/app/growth/kol/page.tsx` — computes\n4686\t    `isActionAllowedForRole(\"kol_rate.update\", actor.role)`\n4687\t    and threads it as `canMutateKolRate` into the table.\n4688\t  - `peek/app/operations/dogpile/page.tsx` — computes the\n4689\t    `dogpile.cancel` and `fraud_flag.status.update` admin\n4690\t    gates and threads them into both tables; lead/hint copy\n4691\t    updated to reflect mutation availability.\n4692\t  - `peek/app/economy/rewards/page.tsx` — computes\n4693\t    `reward_config.update` gate, imports\n4694\t    `PEEK_REWARD_CONFIG_EDITABLE_KEYS`, and threads both into\n4695\t    the table; reward-config hint copy updated.\n4696\t\n4697\t- **Design choices**:\n4698\t  - **Server-side gate is canonical**: `canMutate*` booleans\n4699\t    are computed at the page layer via `isActionAllowedForRole`\n4700\t    (server-only `PEEK_ACTION_RULES`). Tables receive the\n4701\t    boolean — they never re-derive role rules. The server\n4702\t    runner re-checks on dispatch, so even a tampered client\n4703\t    cannot bypass the gate; the prop is purely a visibility\n4704\t    optimization.\n4705\t  - **No-op disablement on reward_config**: `expectedType` and\n4706\t    the FR-14 allowlist are both checked at render time so the\n4707\t    operator UI cannot offer rows the engine would reject; the\n4708\t    submit button additionally disables on no-op input, mirroring\n4709\t    the runner's `noop_value` rule before sending.\n4710\t  - **Form parsing in actions, not in runner**: server actions\n4711\t    coerce `FormData` → typed shape (e.g. `rateBps` to number,\n4712\t    `confirm` to literal `true`) and hand it to\n4713\t    `runPeekMutation` raw so the same zod schema validates UI\n4714\t    and direct callers identically. Coercion failures still\n4715\t    reach the runner as `invalid_input` and emit the\n4716\t    `peek.change.rejected` audit row — the UI cannot silently\n4717\t    drop a failed change.\n4718\t  - **`revalidatePath` per route**: each action revalidates only\n4719\t    its own admin route (`/growth/kol`, `/operations/dogpile`,\n4720\t    `/economy/rewards`) so the post-mutation page reflects the\n4721\t    new DB state without a full reload.\n4722\t\n4723\t- **Targeted checks** (CLAUDE.md TS rule):\n4724\t  - `cd peek && pnpm lint` ✅\n4725\t  - `cd peek && pnpm typecheck` ✅\n4726\t  - `cd peek && pnpm test --run` ✅ (83 files, 968/968 — no\n4727\t    regressions; existing table tests still pass because the\n4728\t    new props default to false / `[]`).\n4729\t\n4730\t- **Next**: `[test] Mutation UI tests: authorized success,\n4731\t  denied actor hidden, validation error display, rejection\n4732\t  feedback.`\n4733\t## Iteration 152 — 2026-04-26 — OK\n4734\t## Iteration 152 — 2026-04-26T19:44:17Z — OK\n4735\t- **Log**: iteration-152.log"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"65159f28-4138-4a00-8878-b10db9efe60e","uuid":"41e860e5-a9f1-4e73-bb91-7d234a1d2a27","timestamp":"2026-04-26T19:44:50.996Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/305-peek-operations-admin/history.md","content":"    (matches the kol-rate `updated_at` precedent).\n\n- **Failure semantics** (surfaced through the runner's execute path):\n  - Disallowed key / malformed value / missing confirmation → schema\n    `invalid_input` before any DB work; `peek.change.rejected` with\n   